strIntroduction:
Via Ferrata is a climbing lane with special safety equipment that offers a different sensation of enjoying the heights. 

Via Ferrata is just like climbing stairs , yet centrally located on a cliff and with safety devices that make rock climbing can be enjoyed by everyone. 

Via Ferrata Derived from the Italian meaning Steel Pathway , began when World War 1 occurs and Italy and Austria are competing to create a passage in the Dolomite mountains to serve as logistic supply trajectory . After the war ended Via ferrata track there serves not only as a tourist destination but also to study the historical sites and the war that had happened . Generally Via Ferrata has become channels of rock climbing with special safety devices that offer the beauty and thrill of climbing without having to have special abilities .

strIntroduction:
Riding on Asia’s longest bi-cable ropeway, you will enjoy the blues and greens of Tung Chung, North Lantau and the South China Sea.

Ngong Ping Cable Car is a visually spectacular 5.7km bi-cable ropeway. As the first of its kind in Hong Kong, the cable car journey begins from Tung Chung, crossing Tung Chung Bay to reach the angle station on Airport Island and turning about 60 degrees in the air towards North Lantau. Visitors will enjoy some of the best views during their joyful 25-minute ride: the vistas of the distant and vast South China Sea and the rolling grassland slopes of North Lantau Country Park from the cable car slowly take over from the hustle and bustle of the city, to introduce our visitors to the serene and natural surrounds that Lantau is famed for. The journey also offers a breathtaking panorama of the Hong Kong International Airport, verdant, mountainous terrain of Lantau Island, Tian Tan Buddha and the 360-degree view of the Ngong Ping Plateau.
